  "text": "We note that the gossip method proposed in [CITATION_1] tackles a similar social learning problem and also possesses properties P1, P2, and P3. In this letter, we take an alternative approach based on evolutionary game theory as opposed to the gossipbased method in [CITATION_2] . The proposed game-theoretic social learning method takes agents' rational learning and decision-making behaviors (such as learning from neighbors with high fitness) into consideration and is thus more amenable to practical implementations in systems with intelligent or strategic agents, e.g., social networks.",
